<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. SUPREME COURT UPHOLDS FLAG BURNING AS PROTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Expressions of conflicting ideology, even when contained in symbolic speech on 
the fringe of the extreme, deserve protection from government sanction. The 
willingness to allow the free exchange of ideas and philosophy is the core of 
the American democratic process. Any decision other than the courageous and 
honorable one refusing to place off limits the ultimate symbol of our declared 
liberty would have been clearly incorrect. 
</P>
<P>
ALVIN M. HALL 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
