<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: RESEARCHER NAMED AS AIDE TO HAYDEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Adi Liberman, the former research director for last year's Proposition O 
campaign to stop onshore drilling, was named administrative assistant in the 
district office of Assemblyman Tom Hayden (D-West Los Angeles). 
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Los Angeles resident was also issues director for Los Angeles 
City Councilman Zev Yaroslavsky's mayoral campaign. Before that, he worked in 
Washington and New Jersey as public affairs director for health care firms. 
</P>
<P>
Liberman is a graduate of Pitzer College in Claremont and earned a master's 
degree from Princeton University's Woodrow Wilson School of Public and 
International Affairs. 
</P>
<P>
He replaces Carol Kurtz, who directed Hayden's district office for five years 
before resigning this month to attend law school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
