<TEXT>
<P>
Part of the City Hall staff, long cramped in tight office space, will be 
moving. 
</P>
<P>
City officials are negotiating with a leasing agency to rent 6,400 square feet 
at an office building next to the new Guest Quarters Hotel, under construction 
on 4th Street behind City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager John Jalili said 33 staffers from the finance and risk management 
departments will move, freeing space inside the cramped, Art Deco City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
The move to Guest Quarters will be temporary, Jalili said. The city is planning 
to build a police station, which means the annex of City Hall now occupied by 
the police will eventually be vacated and made available to city employees. 
</P>
