<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
In an article Thursday on the controversy over Pacific Coast timber harvests, a 
letter urging a moratorium on redwood logging was incorrectly described as 
being signed by 43 members of California's congressional delegation. The letter 
was signed by 18 members of the state's delegation and by 25 House members from 
other states. 
</P>
