<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joseph Remiro, the Symbionese Liberation Army member jailed for killing 
Oakland's school superintendent, has been denied parole, authorities said. 
Remiro, 42, did not attend the Board of Prison Terms hearing at Corcoran State 
Prison. A three-member panel voted unanimously to deny a release date and 
recommended another hearing in two years. Remiro was convicted in 1973 of 
killing Oakland Schools Supt. Marcus Foster with cyanide-tipped bullets. Two 
months later, the SLA, a band of self-described revolutionaries, kidnaped 
newspaper heiress Patricia Hearst. 
