<P>
JAIL REUNITES FATHER, SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A father and son separated since the boy's birth were reunited after 19 years 
when both turned up as inmates in the Santa Clara County Jail. Robert Arthur 
Magoon was in custody for allegedly violating his parole and his father, 
Michael Arthur Magoon, 44, was being held on robbery charges. The elder Magoon 
also has warrants pending for investigation of felony child stealing. "When I 
first came here, they said, 'Do you have a relative here?' " said Robert. "I 
said, 'Not that I know of.' At first, I thought it couldn't be possible. For 
all I knew, he could have been on the other side of the world." Robert was 
separated from his father shortly after birth when his parents split up, and he 
spent most of his youth in foster homes. He ran away from the last one at age 
14. Michael also said he tried looking for his long-lost son and had no idea he 
was in a foster home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
