<TEXT>
<P>
A helicopter crashed on the Greek island of Corfu when it hit the top of a tree 
during filming of the movie "Freedom or Death," killing American stuntman 
Clinton Carpenter, 23, and injuring a five-member film crew, police said. The 
film is being made by British-based All Star Pictures and stars Oliver Reed and 
George Kennedy, police said. Neither actor was involved in the accident. Police 
said the injured on the helicopter were Americans Michael Cane, 30; Phil Odel, 
33, and Lee Linguist, 32. British pilot Mark Wolff, 41, was also injured. 
Hometowns of the victims were not immediately available. 
</P>
