<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FERRARO ASKS SUPPORT FOR FLAG AMENDMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taking up a patriotic cry in response to a recent U.S. Supreme Court ruling, 
Los Angeles City Councilman John Ferraro on Wednesday called on city residents 
to support a constitutional amendment that would outlaw desecration of the 
American flag. 
</P>
<P>
Ferraro introduced his motion after the Supreme Court ruled that flag burning 
is protected under the First Amendment to the Constitution. 
</P>
<P>
Calling the decision "a disappointment to patriotic Americans," the motion asks 
the city to support a resolution authored by State Sen. Cecil Green (D-Santa Fe 
Springs) asking Congress to adopt a constitutional amendment protecting the 
flag. 
</P>
</TEXT>
