<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: BALDWIN PARK; 
</P>
<P>
RUNNING FOR CITY COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents interested in running for the City Council seat vacated by Richard 
Gibson may pick up nomination forms from the city beginning July 17, City Clerk 
Linda Gair said. 
</P>
<P>
Gibson, who had been on the council five years, resigned June 10 to move closer 
to his job in Ventura, where he is a teacher and navigator for the California 
Air National Guard. The council election will be consolidated with the school 
district election Nov. 7. 
</P>
<P>
Interested candidates must file their intent to run by 5 p.m. Aug. 11, Gair 
said. The forms are free, but there is a $25 filing fee, she said. Those who 
would like to include a candidate's statement on the ballot must pay another 
$250, she said. 
</P>
<P>
To qualify, a candidate must be a registered voter and Baldwin Park resident 
who has not been convicted of a felony, Gair said. Forms may be picked up from 
the city clerk at 14403 Pacific Ave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
