</P>
<P>
IMELDA SINGS TO DYING MARCOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONOLULU 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A tearful Imelda Marcos quietly sang a love song today to her husband, ousted 
Philippine President Ferdinand E. Marcos, as he lay close to death. 
</P>
<P>
"We are praying for a miracle," she said. "If I could just tell him he could go 
back home (to the Philippines), I know this would save him." 
</P>
<P>
The Philippine bedside song, "How Much I love You," appeared to get a response 
from the deposed president, in a semi-comatose state with kidney, heart and 
lung failure. He opened his eyes and squeezed his wife's hand, friends claimed. 
</P>
<P>
Philippine President Corazon Aquino has refused repeated requests by Marcos to 
return to his homeland to die. 
</P>
</TEXT>
