<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN BURNS FLAG IN DISPUTE OVER JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OSHKOSH, Wis. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 28-year-old jobless man burned an American flag outside a University of 
Wisconsin-Oshkosh building today, saying it was a protest over his not being 
allowed to work at the campus radio station. 
</P>
<P>
Asked why he was burning the flag, David Machen said: "It is because the flag 
has been identified as the promise of the rights granted in the Constitution 
that are now being, I believe, grossly violated in my case by an official of 
the state of Wisconsin." 
</P>
<P>
Machen said he was involved in physical fights with station personnel when he 
worked at the station in 1978 and 1981. He blamed an "emotional condition" and 
said it has since been corrected. 
</P>
