<P>
MONTES KEEPS TITLE WITH KNOCKOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Montes defended his California junior welterweight title with a 
third-round knockout over Kenny Comer in their scheduled 12-round state title 
bout Wednesday night at the Hollywood Palladium. 
</P>
<P>
The 140-pound Montes, of Anaheim, hit Comer, 139 pounds, with a strong left 
hook and followed with combinations to the head and body before referee Kenny 
Davis stopped the fight at 2:30 of the third round. Montes raised his record to 
44-5, 30 wins by knockout. 
</P>
<P>
In San Diego, Ysaias Zamudio of Blythe won a 12-round unanimous decision over 
Martin Cardenas of Tijuana Wednesday night to retain the World Boxing Assn. 
America's flyweight championship. 
</P>
<P>
In another title bout, Tim Williams of San Diego defended his California 
middleweight title for the third time with a 12-round majority decision over 
Roberto Rosiles of Blythe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
